review:
[u] What was promised: [/u]
-PvE with full story campaign and hero missions;
-Graphical update, including full remaster of old skins;
-Time of day on all maps;
-Scoreboard.

[u] What was delivered: [/u]
-3 campaign missions for 15 bucks (no hero missions);
-Ambient Occlusion and all new skins are slightly higher resolution;
-Time of day only on few selected maps;
-Scoreboard.

[u] What was removed (since OW1): [/u]
-Endgame cards;
-Medals;
-On fire (brought back in S5);
-Player progression;
-Lootboxes;
-LFG System;
-2CP;
-Archives Event;
-Papa Jeff.

[u] What was paywalled (since OW1): [/u]
-All skins (old ones are now obtainable as one legendary per season);
-New heroes;

[u] What's also feels worse (since OW1): [/u]
-Cinematics (that marvel level humor and rap are feel completely off);
-Push (yes, it's worse for 2CP);
-New UI;
-New heroes (generic and cringe);
-Events (only 2 new legendaries per event instead of 6, and both of them are paywalled);
-Game now has tons of bugs, including broken lightning and cubemapping on few maps;
-New hero select animations (feels like they were done on cheap outsource).

[h1] I've been scammed from OW1 I paid for and it's fair play to earn system, and I've been scammed from PvE they promised me. They DOUBLE SCAMMED ME from both things that was holding me in the game. Go better play TF2. [/h1]
